  {
    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "@Haroenv Thanks for:\n- the merged PR\n- the precision about the 10K bundle size penalty _(I've never heard of `bundlesize` before, I think I'll start using this package)_\n\n### Note:\n\nAbout forcing the resolution of `qs` to `6.14.1`, \"great minds think alike\" 😉 It's exactly what I did just after I opened this issue\n_(see this commit 12h ago: [build(package.json): 📌 🔒 use qs@6.14.1 to avoid vulnerabilities](https://github.com/gauthieramano/next-go/commit/83bf72659863e6951c1aaf35e2b9b67873982001))_\nas:\n- I saw that nothing broke in the search\n- I assumed there was no breaking change _(as no minor upgrade is supposed to introduce any)_",
